pert JVM test engineer specializing in high-coverage integration testing for external libraries.\\n1992:  Improve test coverage for the active dynamic-access class in `jspapi:jsp-api:2.0-20040521`.\\n2003:  - Class: javax.servlet.jsp.tagext.SimpleTagSupport\\n2004:  - Source file: SimpleTagSupport.java\\n2012:  - [reflection] java.lang.Class#forName(java.lang.String) <- javax._06272339748e5c580169f51660ff6c819fb1016d1ea120719a\\\", \\\"toolName\\\": \\\"bash\\\", \\\"content\\\": [{\\\"type\\\": \\\"text\\\", \\\"text\\\": \\\"forge/DEVELOPING.md:98:  [--keep-tests-without-dynamic-access] \\\\\\\\\\\\nforge/DEVELOPING.md:123:- `--keep-tests-without-dynamic-access` keeps generated tests for dynamic-access workflows even if no dynamic-access call sites are covered.\\\\nforge/DEVELOPING.md:409:The `dynamic_access_iterative` workflow improves metadata accuracy by using the `generateDynamicAccessCoverageReport` Gradle task to identify which dynamic-access call sites (reflection, JNI, resources, serialization) are not yet covered by the generated tests. Instead of generating tests blindly, the workflow iterates class-by-class, sending the agent targeted prompts with the exact uncovered call sites for each class. After each attempt, the report is regenerated and coverage deltas are computed to decide whether to retry the same class or move on.\\\\nforge/DEVELOPING.md:411:If the library has no dynamic access, the workflow falls back to the standard `basic_iterative` strategy automatically.\\\\nforge/DEVELOPING.md:440:Composite strategies (run a primary workflow, then refine dynamic-access coverage):\\\\nforge/DEVELOPING.md:447:#### Running a dynamic-access strategy\\\\nforge/DEVELOPING.md:469:For the detailed function-level notes and sequence diagram, see `docs/dynamic-access-strategy.md`.\\\\nforge/forge_metadata.py:1768:    \\\\\\\"\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\"Load dynamic-access coverage from the stored run metrics stats block.\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\"\\\\nforge/forge_metadata.py:1784:    covered_calls = int(dynamic_access.get(\\\\\\\"coveredCalls\\\\\\\", 0) or 0)\\\\nforge/forge_metadata.py:1798:    \\\\\\\"\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\"Resolve the dynamic-access coverage report path for a new-library issue.\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\"\\\\nforge/forge_metadata.py:1809:        \\\\\\\"dynamic-access\\\\\\\",\\\\nforge/forge_metadata.py:1810:        \\\\\\\"dynamic-access-coverage.json\\\\\\\",\\\\nforge/forge_metadata.py:1815:    \\\\\\\"\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\"Load dynamic-access coverage directly from the generated report as a fallback.\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\"\\\\nforge/forge_metadata.py:1942:        \\\\\\\"Analyze the generated tests, metadata, stats, and dynamic-access report in this repository. \\\\\\\"\\\\nforge/forge_metadata.py:1946:        \\\\\\\"- Explain briefly why dynamic-access coverage is missing or still very low.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\"\\\\nforge/forge_metadata.py:1965:        f\\\\\\\"Automation completed for `{claimed_issue.issue_coordinates}`, but dynamic-access coverage remains \\\\\\\"\\\\nforge/forge_metadata.py:1967:        \\\\\\\"This suggests the generated tests are not exercising the required dynamic-access paths well enough.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\"\\\\nforge/forge_metadata.py:1969:        \\\\\\\"- Inspect the generated tests and compare them with the dynamic-access report to find uncovered call sites.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\"\\\\nforge/forge_metadata.py:2631:            pipeline_argv.append(\\\\\\\"--keep-tests-without-dynamic-access\\\\\\\")\\\\nforge/forge_metadata.py:4537:        \\\\\\\"--keep-tests-without-dynamic-access\\\\\\\",\\\\nforge/forge_metadata.py:4540:            \\\\\\\"Forwarded to the new-library pipeline. Keeps generated tests for dynamic-access \\\\\\\"\\\\nforge/forge_metadata.py:4541:            \\\\\\\"strategies even when no dynamic-access coverage is added.\\\\\\\"\\\\nforge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:62:      \\\\\\\"dynamic-access-iteration\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"prompt_templates/dynamic_access/dynamic-access-iteration