\\n**Exploring coverage issues**\\\\n\\\\nI’m wondering if the problem arises because the `klass` Class object has a compile-time exact type known to the static analyzer, while JVM coverage doesn't reflect that. It seems dynamic access coverage might be measured by the agent during native runtime. Notably, the native tests ran three times with no coverage. To cover a call site, I might need to run `Class.forName` at runtime. It seems complex, especially if the image initializes certain fields at build time. I think I need to explore dynamic class loading options within the limitations.\\\\n\\\\n**Investigating API coverage**\\\\n\\\\nI realize the library's public API requires a Class object, but typical usage just passes `SomeClass.class`. I need to cover the library's `Class.forName` method, not the test itself. It might be that the native image constant folds definitions because static fields are initialized at build time, rather than due to parameter constants. I wonder if using `--initialize-at-run-time=javax.servlet.jsp.tagext.TagSupport` is allowed. For the coverage report, I should also consider JaCoCo's line coverage from JVM tests. Examining the class file compiled with debug line 80 could provide more insights.\\\", \\\"thinkingSignature\\\": \\\"{\\\\\\\"id\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"rs_06272339748e5c580169f516632f6c819f9f1e2bd8a9208aa9\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"type\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"reasoning\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"encrypted_content\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"gAAAAABp9RZv1Tav5TvhE60LZXSaOTnJ0S89wgt7eVcviLczLW7H2YOXuVopBx5GXsfHKx5zX4q2MnkzPjWJ0He-LSVAiUetlfDva2uJtKX2wG_AvS4DCee9EZDIe8qXg06jamelfZbZZiK00MgCSkzhu9zyboLntLwCzPoKovbj8luvEd2XUndDL8k_QyZC6XM-LH63S8L0zkqXvfke9qT1nlxINbD4p1H4YMqBOMDMXQUL2jKSRKsy6DPmDOZbpBOr-_r57g2P2pArkyTT3Vnu_B7sXkTUOKAD0k6ApGJUhIYg88MetyWm_0Qii6KbCQKIhGM6JeYtT10uQNX5PmG8L2kCWLlg0qfzbHw2_FUtmsVV5WgFTVb6dFGm9WYn67dlcDETSpp88IA1XbSijpytv8bJmvrJnFxEaYISTAALzBsg5wdFDxv25s5FLGAs__Kq3YjBc6qJuJp8WsVrOT2zoBQzApWYpXE1G123cSys0NdqDQqRBA00WUOkVd9sbGvrD1ifMwpi_FPUFgpI_WOj9Vuben0